Infrastructure Requirements

Hardware: 4 vCPU, 16GB RAM, 200GB storage per node (2-node cluster minimum)
Software: Docker, Kubernetes, JDK 11, PostgreSQL
Network: Load balancer, WAF, SSL certificates, VPN to core banking
Storage: Object storage for documents with encryption at rest
Third-Party: eKYC provider, biometric service, AML screening provider



Compliance and Security

Standards: REST APIs, OAuth2, OpenID Connect, JSON/XML
Security: Biometric authentication, JWT tokens, mTLS, end-to-end encryption
Compliance: NBE KYC requirements, AML regulations, Data Protection laws
Auditing: Complete audit trail for all onboarding transactions






































Recommendation

As aforementioned, we tried to explicitly elaborate and set the recommendation for the Bank to decide on the path to move towards by having the mission and vision of the Bank into consideration.

We strongly recommend APPROACH 1: DEDICATED MOBILE APPLICATION for the following reasons:

Superior User Experience: The dedicated app provides a focused, distraction-free onboarding journey that achieves 25% higher conversion rates compared to embedded solutions.

Optimal Performance: With a lightweight footprint (~25MB vs 100MB+), the dedicated app works efficiently on older devices and low-bandwidth conditions, expanding the addressable customer base.

Maximum Flexibility: Independent release cycles enable rapid iteration, A/B testing, and market-specific customizations without impacting core banking operations.

Security Isolation: A separate application provides dedicated security controls and reduces the attack surface for sensitive onboarding data.

Faster Time to Market: The dedicated app can be deployed in 32 weeks versus 36 weeks for the integration approach.

If the recommendation is to use a Dedicated Mobile Application, it provides a customer-centric and flexible solution for acquiring and onboarding new customers efficiently. With its focused user experience and independent architecture, the dedicated app can support the bank's growth and competitiveness in the digital banking landscape. Therefore, we recommend for the Bank to implement APPROACH 1: DEDICATED MOBILE APPLICATION and considering the advantage of having a reliable, secure, and controllable environment for customer onboarding.

Overall, our recommendations are as follows:

Bank shall implement DEDICATED MOBILE APPLICATION for Customer Onboarding
The bank shall engage implementer for standardized and effective implementation and adoption
Bank shall choose deployment approach of type, cloud-native with on-premises core banking integration
Bank shall setup center of excellence, Digital Onboarding Team
Bank shall align/setup training for Digital Onboarding Team
Bank shall initiate technical discussion with eKYC and biometric service providers
Bank shall integrate with WSO2 ESB and API Manager for backend services